WEBVTT

00:06.631 --> 00:09.426
Dang, son! I'm killing
this budget spreadsheet.

00:10.885 --> 00:12.262
Being an adult is sad.

00:16.224 --> 00:17.100
I get that.

00:19.519 --> 00:22.063
I have returned.

00:22.147 --> 00:23.857
Dang. What happened to your nose?

00:23.940 --> 00:26.818
I went shoe-shopping with your mother.

00:27.819 --> 00:29.320
Yeah, that tracks.

00:29.404 --> 00:31.823
I'm just lucky Lydia came prepared.

00:32.323 --> 00:34.325
I told you I still need tampons.

00:36.327 --> 00:38.496
Abuelita, you got the shoes!

00:38.580 --> 00:40.498
You're my hero. Thank you.

00:41.082 --> 00:42.000
You're welcome.

00:42.083 --> 00:44.544
I really had to fight for them.

00:44.627 --> 00:45.795
Mami, we talked about this.

00:45.879 --> 00:48.631
-You cannot keep spoiling Alex.
-I'm not.

00:48.715 --> 00:51.593
I just went to pick them up for him
because he is still grounded.

00:51.676 --> 00:55.805
No, no. He paid with his own $300.

00:55.889 --> 00:59.851
Three hundred dollars
for one pair of shoes?

00:59.934 --> 01:02.479
They better come
with $280 stuffed in them!

01:10.028 --> 01:12.405
Mom, I did exactly what you told me to do.

01:12.489 --> 01:14.574
You said that if I wanted
to buy expensive shoes,

01:14.657 --> 01:16.201
I had to earn my own money.

01:16.951 --> 01:18.203
I did say that.

01:19.245 --> 01:21.748
Lesson number two.
Don't buy stupid stuff. Come here.

01:24.334 --> 01:27.879
Look at my credit card statement.
Every dollar is budgeted.

01:27.962 --> 01:30.381
Four hundred dollars a month
for groceries,

01:30.465 --> 01:32.425
sixty dollars to keep the lights on,

01:32.509 --> 01:34.844
seven dollars at the Fountain Hotel.

01:34.928 --> 01:36.012
What?

01:36.721 --> 01:38.431
That's not my charge.

01:38.515 --> 01:40.266
Somebody must've stolen
my credit card number.

01:40.350 --> 01:42.143
For seven dollars?

01:42.227 --> 01:44.145
Not how I would have played it.

01:44.229 --> 01:46.648
No, no, no. This is what they do.

01:46.731 --> 01:50.401
They start by racking up little charges
to make sure the card works.

01:50.485 --> 01:53.113
Macy's, Nike, Harley-Davidson.

01:53.196 --> 01:55.490
Then you realize
they're living your best life.

01:57.826 --> 01:58.993
Did you cancel the card?

01:59.077 --> 02:01.329
No, I wanted to see
what I would have done next.

02:03.873 --> 02:07.085
Listen, I have never even
been to your hotel.

02:07.168 --> 02:09.462
It's a minibar charge?
You really got the wrong girl.

02:10.672 --> 02:14.509
What are you gonna accuse me of next?
Not washing and reusing tinfoil?

02:16.803 --> 02:18.638
What was the name on the credit card?

02:19.347 --> 02:21.724
Elena Alvarez? Wait!

02:26.354 --> 02:27.230
[Penelope] Thank you.

02:28.106 --> 02:29.899
Hi!

02:32.777 --> 02:35.738
Why did you use your emergency
credit card at the Fountain Hotel?

02:35.822 --> 02:37.282
And what were you even doing there?

02:37.365 --> 02:38.700
A few people had died there.

02:38.783 --> 02:39.993
I was ghost hunting.

02:42.912 --> 02:44.330
-No, you weren't.
-No, I wasn't.

02:45.623 --> 02:47.876
Elena, come on. Be honest.

02:52.881 --> 02:54.883
[clears throat]
Syd and I got a hotel room.

02:55.842 --> 02:57.177
Why would you need...

03:10.857 --> 03:11.733
Uh...

03:21.659 --> 03:23.578
I can't believe you used the minibar.

03:29.876 --> 03:31.127
And you know, you...

03:31.878 --> 03:34.839
We're going to circle back
around to all of this.

03:36.841 --> 03:38.343
Mami, where are you going?

03:38.927 --> 03:40.303
I'm not quite sure.

03:44.766 --> 03:46.100
